  "prompt": "Is it appropriate for a (Christian) spouse to refuse to pray with their spouse or go to church services with the spouse anytime they have an argument?",
  "response": "This is not considered a healthy or biblical approach to resolving marital conflicts. In Christian marriages, communication, forgiveness, and mutual support are important, even during disagreements. Withholding spiritual intimacy as a form of punishment or manipulation goes against biblical principles of love, unity, and reconciliation. \n\nHealthy Christian marriages should:\n1. Communicate openly and respectfully\n2. Seek to resolve conflicts constructively\n3. Maintain spiritual connection, especially during difficult times\n4. Practice forgiveness\n5. Support each other's spiritual growth\n\nIf conflicts are persistent or significant, couples might benefit from:\n- Marriage counseling\n- Pastoral guidance\n- Couples' prayer and communication workshops\n- Individual and joint spiritual growth\n\nThe Bible encourages spouses to love, honor, and support each other, even during challenging times (Ephesians 4:2-3, 1 Corinthians 13:4-7).",
